feat: LS 2024 data + representation mapping + cross-cycle comparison views + UX polish

Major changes since the last commit, grouped by feature area.

─── LS 2024 data pipeline (new) ────────────────────────────────────
• Parsed ECI GE-2024 statistical-report XLS files (File #34
  "Details of Assembly Segment of PC" + File #6 "List of Successful
  Candidates") into per-state JSON.
• Ingested AC-segment-wise LS 2024 results into HistoricalResult
  (year=2024) — 6,760 rows across 824 ACs.
• Ingested all 116 LS 2024 MP names + party + demographics into
  new mp_2024_* columns on LokSabhaSeat.
• New scripts: scripts/parse_2024_ls.py, scripts/parse_2024_ls_mps.py,
  scripts/ingest_2024_ls.py, scripts/ingest_2024_ls_mps.py.
• Raw XLS files gitignored (13 MB) — parsed JSON committed.

─── MP ↔ MLA representation mapping (new) ──────────────────────────
• Backend: /{state}/constituency/{ac_number} now returns a
  "representation" block pairing the AC's 2026 MLA with the parent
  LS seat's 2024 MP.
• Backend: /{state}/loksabha includes sitting_mp_2024 per seat.
• Frontend: new "Who Represents You" card on ConstituencyDetail
  showing MLA + MP side-by-side with demographic chips.
• Frontend: sitting MP banner inside the Geography LS-seat detail.

─── LS 2024 actual vs 2026 projection (new) ────────────────────────
• Backend: new endpoint /{state}/ls2024-pc-winners returning the
  actual LS 2024 MP per PC + full alliance/party breakdown.
• Frontend: new Ls2024VsProjectionCard with:
  - Filterable chips ("X same" / "Y would flip" toggle as filters).
  - Two-row tally bars (LS24 vs 2026 projection).
  - Clickable rows opening a detail modal with side-by-side
    alliance breakdowns, the sitting MP banner, and a plain-English
    "story" sentence.

─── LS-segment churn comparisons (refactor) ────────────────────────
• Backend: /{state}/ls-segment-swing now parameterised by baseline
  year — added /{state}/ls2024-vs-a2026-swing for the LS24 → A2026
  churn variant.
• Frontend: District + LS-segment churn cards MOVED from Swing &
  Trends to Geography (district churn under District View tab,
  LS-segment churns under Lok Sabha View tab).
• Frontend: new "Compare LS Outcomes" sub-tab picker inside the
  Geography LS tab — three comparison views (LS24 vs Projection,
  AC-segment churn 2021→2026, AC-segment churn LS24→A26) now live
  behind one tab strip instead of stacking three near-identical
  tables.

─── DistrictChurnCard cleanup ──────────────────────────────────────
• Narrative summary line at the top ("X districts saw a leadership
  change — gained by BJP (12); Y kept their 2021 leader").
• Replaced 3 numeric columns (Flipped / Held / Churn%) with a
  single stacked visual bar + count.
• New "Leadership" status badge column showing party change at a
  glance (orange "PartyA → PartyB" pill or green "✓ PartyX held").
• Parametrised title / subtitle / columnLabel / prevLabel /
  groupNoun so the same card renders for District, LS-segment, and
  LS24-vs-A26 contexts.
• Bug fix: 2021-leader column was gated on "leader_seats_2021 > 0"
  (the 2026 winner's 2021 count) which hid the actual 2021 leader
  when a party swept. Now shows the real top 2021 party.

─── MLA Profile by Party (Parties page) ────────────────────────────
• New tabbed card "MLA Profile by Party" with Age / Assets /
  Criminal Cases views — stacked distributions per party with
  averages on the right.
• Backend (/{state}/party-analytics): added mla_age_distribution,
  mla_asset_distribution, mla_criminal_distribution + supporting
  avg/median/coverage fields.
• Shows every party with ≥1 MLA. Renders a "no data on file"
  striped placeholder for parties whose affidavit is missing, plus
  a footer warning with total missing-MLA count — transparency on
  ADR coverage gaps.
• Cleaner color ramps (Age: cyan→teal→amber→orange→crimson;
  Assets: slate→teal→blue→indigo→magenta; Criminal: punchier
  green→red), taller bars + bolder labels.

─── Overview cards ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Vote-to-seat conversion tile promoted from Swing to Overview
  (sits next to Seat Tally) — surfaces "FPTP arithmetic" insight
  on the landing page.

─── Assets page enrichment ─────────────────────────────────────────
• New "Wealth Distribution" histogram: 6 wealth tiers (<₹0.5cr →
  ₹100cr+), each bar split into winners (striped overlay) vs
  losers (solid) for visual signal of where MLAs cluster.
• New "Do Winners Have More Money?" card: avg + median for winners
  vs losers, with auto-adjusted callout sentence ("The average
  winner is X× wealthier than the average loser", or the inverse
  finding when voters chose the less-wealthy candidate).

─── Bug fixes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
• LS 2024 winner attribution was computing alliance-summed top
  under the 2026 alliance config, which produced fictional alliance
  totals (e.g. TN AIADMK + BJP under 2026's NDA-TN, even though
  AIADMK was independent in LS 2024). Fixed to use the actual
  ECI-declared MP's party mapped to its 2026 alliance. Now matches
  reality across all 5 states (TN: SPA 39/39, KL: UDF 18/LDF 1/NDA
  1, WB: AITC 29/NDA 12/INC 1, AS: NDA 10/INC 3/Other 1, PY: INC 1).
• Geography deep-link scroll: handles the three new LS sub-tab
  hashes (#ls-segment-churn, #ls24-vs-a26-churn, #ls2024-vs-
  projection) and auto-selects the matching sub-tab before scroll.
• Overview anti-incumbency "see district churn" link now points at
  /geography#district-churn (was /swing#district-churn).

─── Config / data ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
• Added KEC (ECI's abbreviation for Kerala Congress, won Kottayam
  via Francis George) to Kerala UDF alliance config.
• .gitignore: added data/eci_2024_ls/*.xls / *.xlsx (large raw
  inputs kept local), data/election.db.before_* (DB backups).
